---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "AboutPage",
    "name": "How Sonura Works With Artists",
    "description": "Sonura is built on the consent side of AI music: licensed, commercially-cleared technology rather than scraped catalogs.",
    "url": "https://sonurastudio.com/how-we-work-with-artists/"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://sonurastudio.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "How We Work With Artists", "item": "https://sonurastudio.com/how-we-work-with-artists/" }
    ]
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How Sonura Works With Artists | Licensed, Consent-First AI Music"
  description="AI music split in two: one side scrapes artists' work without asking, the other is built on licensed foundations. Sonura sits on the consent side. Here is what that means."
  keywords="ethical ai music, licensed ai music, consent ai music, how ai music is trained, is ai music stolen, ai music artist consent"
  canonical="https://sonurastudio.com/how-we-work-with-artists/"
  ogTitle="How Sonura Works With Artists"
  ogDescription="Sonura is built on the consent side of AI music: licensed foundations, not scraped catalogs."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <style>
    .aw { max-width: 760px; margin: 96px auto 120px; padding: 0 24px; }
    .aw-hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .aw-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(34px, 6vw, 52px); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--fg); }
    .aw-hero p { color: var(--muted); font-size: clamp(17px, 2.2vw, 20px); line-height: 1.65; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .aw-section { padding-top: 48px; margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .aw-section h2 { font-size: clamp(22px, 3.5vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 18px; color: var(--fg); }
    .aw-section p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 18px; }
    .aw-section strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
    .aw-points { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 4px 0 0; }
    .aw-points li { position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; }
    .aw-points li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 11px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--fg); opacity: 0.35; }
    .aw-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 64px; padding-top: 56px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .aw-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(24px, 4vw, 32px); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px; color: var(--fg); }
    .aw-cta p { color: var(--muted); max-width: 520px; margin: 0 auto 28px; line-height: 1.65; }
    .aw p a, .aw-points a { color: var(--fg); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; text-decoration-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3); }
    .aw p a:hover, .aw-points a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--fg); }
    .aw .button.primary { background: var(--fg); color: var(--bg); text-decoration: none; }
    .aw .button.primary:hover { background: #fff; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  </style>

  <div class="aw">
    <header class="aw-hero">
      <h1>How we work with artists</h1>
      <p>AI music has split into two worlds. One scrapes artists' work without asking. The other is built on licensed foundations. Sonura is built on the second.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="aw-section">
      <h2>Built on consent, not scraping</h2>
      <p>The real divide in AI music isn't "AI or no AI." It's consent. Some models are trained on music scraped from the internet without permission, the approach at the center of the major-label lawsuits. Others are trained on licensed material, where the people who own the music agreed to take part.</p>
      <p><strong>Sonura is built on licensed, commercially-cleared music technology, not scraped catalogs.</strong> The music behind the sounds you create was licensed, not taken.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="aw-section">
      <h2>AI is the engine. You're the artist.</h2>
      <p>Sonura is a tool, not a replacement for you. It creates the raw material, beats, loops, vocals, one-shots, stems, and then you do the part that makes it music: choose, arrange, edit, and finish it in your DAW. The taste and the decisions are yours.</p>
      <p>That's why we build around <a href="/features/stem-export/">editable stems</a> instead of one-click finished songs. Building blocks keep you in control of the result.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="aw-section">
      <h2>What this means for you</h2>
      <ul class="aw-points">
        <li><strong>You own what you make.</strong> Full commercial rights to release the beats, loops, and stems you create.</li>
        <li><strong>Cleared for commercial use.</strong> Built for real releases, client work, and content, not a legal grey area.</li>
        <li><strong>You're not building on stolen work.</strong> Your track rests on a licensed foundation.</li>
        <li><strong>You stay the author.</strong> AI speeds up the process; the creative decisions stay with you.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="aw-cta">
      <h2>Make music you can stand behind</h2>
      <p>Create editable beats, loops, vocals, and stems on a licensed foundation, and finish them your way.</p>
      <a href="https://app.sonurastudio.com/studio" class="button primary large">Start Creating Free</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
